Merge pull request #23 from johntyree/bug/multiplatform-tests

Fix process_lock and tests on Win32
TST: add missing import
TST: remove print statement
TST: skip multi-opening file handle test on win32

TST: crank up the timeout for external lock tests

Windows is really slow, especially in a VM.
TST: warn when processes timeout
TST: check exitcodes of child processes
TST: properly scope child processes and get them working on windows

TST: make _do_test_lock_externally work on Windows

We need to access the platform-specific file handle locking
mechanisms, but they are hidden away in the class implementations.

This pushes them into static methods to make it easy to access them
while still allowing sub-classing.

TST: move try_lock helper to toplevel

Windows apparently can't pickle this properly otherwise.
TST: skip complicated POSIX-only interprocess test
TST: fix multiplatform support for process lock tests
